1
00:00:01,515 --> 00:00:13,125
[SPEAKER_11]: Start March 29th, 2023 governor Haley signed into law a supplemental budget bill with, among other things, extends the temporary provisions pertaining to the open meeting law to March 31st, 2025.

2
00:00:13,185 --> 00:00:23,895
[SPEAKER_11]: Typically, this further extension allows public bodies holding meetings remotely without a quorum of the public body physically present at a meeting location and to provide adequate alternative access to remote meetings.

3
00:00:24,580 --> 00:00:33,102
[SPEAKER_11]: The language does not make any substantive changes to the open meeting while extending the expiration date and temporary provisions regarding remote meetings from March 31st, 2023 to March 31st, 2025.

4
00:00:33,142 --> 00:00:33,402
[SPEAKER_11]: Great.

5
00:00:37,343 --> 00:00:37,903
[SPEAKER_05]: Thanks, Dennis.

6
00:00:38,663 --> 00:00:45,345
[SPEAKER_05]: I then will call the meeting to order at 635 on August 16th, 2023.

7
00:00:47,345 --> 00:00:51,987
