601
00:57:33,994 --> 00:57:49,580
[SPEAKER_01]: Hello, my name is Peter Bacchus and I'm a project environmental scientist with Ty and Bond here on behalf of Eversource Energy and sorry, just bringing my screen up really quick.

602
00:57:49,960 --> 00:57:50,260
[SPEAKER_01]: There we go.

603
00:57:52,098 --> 00:57:57,503
[SPEAKER_01]: Also on the call, I have Brian Gammons with Tie and Bond, who's a senior environmental scientist on this project.

604
00:57:57,743 --> 00:58:01,566
[SPEAKER_01]: And we have Sean Grant from DCR on here as well.

605
00:58:03,128 --> 00:58:15,319
[SPEAKER_01]: So we are looking to request an amended order of conditions for the underground electric transmission project to build a bicycle path extension in the area around the Medford Community Gardens.

606
00:58:16,860 --> 00:58:26,366
[SPEAKER_01]: So just a little background on this in order conditions was originally issued in 2017 for the project and then extended in 2020 and 2023 as construction continued.

607
00:58:27,286 --> 00:58:34,090
[SPEAKER_01]: At this point, the transmission lines installed work is substantially complete and across the line restoration is underway.

608
00:58:35,611 --> 00:58:37,832
[SPEAKER_01]: While digging through kind of the restoration and prepping it.

609
00:58:38,993 --> 00:58:59,671
[SPEAKER_01]: we were reviewing documents and a construction access permit that was given by DCR was reviewed and realized that we didn't have the bicycle pathway that this permit required on the restoration plans as this whole process kind of took place concurrent with the NOI filing, but was not approved until after the order of conditions had been issued.

610
00:59:00,091 --> 00:59:02,373
[SPEAKER_01]: So we realized in the restoration plans we were missing this.

611
00:59:02,813 --> 00:59:06,176
[SPEAKER_01]: So we wanted to come back to the commission and request an order of conditions

612
00:59:07,197 --> 00:59:10,102
[SPEAKER_01]: Sorry, Amendment to the Order of Conditions to include this pathway.

613
00:59:10,122 --> 00:59:10,162
[SPEAKER_01]: So.

614
00:59:13,721 --> 00:59:14,402
[SPEAKER_01]: What do you call it?

615
00:59:14,522 --> 00:59:19,647
[SPEAKER_01]: We met with Dennis at first, because we weren't sure if we were going to go the NOI route or this amendment order.

616
00:59:19,707 --> 00:59:22,610
[SPEAKER_01]: We realized, well, we would have overlapping footprints here.

617
00:59:23,891 --> 00:59:25,833
[SPEAKER_01]: And I'll show these on the screen in a little bit.

618
00:59:25,933 --> 00:59:28,795
[SPEAKER_01]: So we thought that amending the current order was better.

619
00:59:28,815 --> 00:59:31,818
[SPEAKER_01]: We still notified butters and all of the process.

620
00:59:32,839 --> 00:59:38,604
[SPEAKER_01]: So we just didn't want to start scratch for the new NOI and have two conflicting order of conditions on the same geographic footprint.

621
00:59:39,665 --> 00:59:42,246
[SPEAKER_01]: So we are still falling under some area subject to jurisdiction.

622
00:59:43,106 --> 00:59:44,987
[SPEAKER_01]: So that's why we're back.

623
00:59:46,348 --> 00:59:49,028
[SPEAKER_01]: So just a little overview of what we're requesting.

624
00:59:49,609 --> 00:59:55,511
[SPEAKER_01]: This is the intersection of Winthrop Street, north-south here and Mystic Valley Parkway heading east-west, top of the screen.

625
00:59:55,911 --> 00:59:58,192
[SPEAKER_01]: The community gardens are available here.

626
00:59:58,492 --> 00:59:59,932
